page.title: 04CARNOUSTIE FLORA AND FAUNA
page.content: A walk in the woods round about reveals a variety of trees, plants and wild-life. We visited a wooded area in May and here is what we found. The predominant tree was the {beech,}with its new coat of pale green leaves. There were also some{birch trees, and the occasional{hawthorn, {lime}and{sycamore. There were signs that birds had been nesting in the wood, as the shell of a blackbird's egg was found.{Sparrows, {blackbirds}and{wood pigeons}were the most common birds seen. {Daffodils}and{bluebells}were growing in places and the odd patch of {heather. It was rather damp underfoot and the ditches which ran through the wood were full of water. A thick layer of {moss}made the ground very soft and springy.
